Delafield, Wisconsin is located among the tranquil water and rolling hills of Waukesha County’s “Lake Country," just between Milwaukee and Madison. It's the ideal launching point for outdoor fun with fishing and boating on the lakes, golfing, miles of hiking and biking trails and so much more! Experience theatre under the stars, art walks, and music festivals are just a few ways to enjoy Delafield. Of course, there's a fine selection of dining and one-of-a-kind shopping too! Smiles await you in Delafield.

The heart of Delafield is its historic downtown with one-of-a-kind boutiques and restaurants. Just a short drive down Milwaukee Street, you’ll come upon the bustling commercial center, with an inviting mix of local restaurants and popular favorites and convenient shopping to suit every need.

Delafield is located off I-94 between Milwaukee and Madison in Waukesha County. There are two exits off the interstate I-94 for Delafield:  The Hwy C exit will lead you to historic downtown Delafield, and the Hwy 83 exit will lead you to the commercial shopping district of Delafield. The north side of Delafield's commercial shopping center is located on the corners of Hwy 16 and Hwy 83.

content=Developed in 1986, the Glacial Drumlin State Trail is one of Wisconsin's best bicycle trails. Starting in Cottage Grove, the 52 miles trail goes east to connect with other trails in the Fox River Sanctuary in Waukesha, WI. The trail is open cyclists, walkers, joggers and roller-bladers.

content=The 8-mile Lake Country Recreation Trail is located on the former Milwaukee - Watertown Interurban Railway. The trail stretches between the Landsberg Center trailhead and Cushing Park in the City of Delafield.
